a language for treating geometric patterns in a twodimensional space in this paper cadep a problemoriented language for positioning geometric patterns in a twodimensional  space is presented  although the language has been specifically designed for the automatic generation  of integrated circuit masks it turns out to be well suited also for such other placement problems as  architecture design urban planning logical and block diagram representation  the design criteria  the structure and the specific features of cadep are illustrated cacm january 1971 bracchi g ferrari d 